# File and Disk Management

## Lab Overview
This lab explores how to browse directories and move files

## Objectives
- Understand different methods of navigating CLI directories
- Identify useful commands for managing files
- Explain how these tools are useful for cybersecurity

## Key Concepts

| cd(change directory) | displays the current drive and folder(directory) |
| dir | shows the folders and files inside the current folder(directory) |
| tree | displays directories and subdirectories in a tree-like format |
| mkdir | creates a new folder |
| rmdir | deletes a folder, if it is empty |
| type | displays the contents of a readable txt. file |
| copy | makes a duplicate of a file in the same location |
| move | moves the original file or folder to a another location, can also rename a file |
| *(wildcard) | means show all items related to the command and parameters |

