- 0 File(s) means there are currently no files in the current folder
- 0 bytes because there are no data files, if there were files then it would show the total data amount in bytes
- 11 Dir(s) is the total amount of directories
- 14,984,953,856 bytes free(the total amount of free space on the C: drive)
- syntax: dir /a(will display hidden systems and files)
- syntax: dir /s(will display files in the current directory including any sub directories of the current directory

