## Security Relevance
- administrators, security professionals and malicous actors interact with file systems
- the ability to inspect, move and identify the contents of file systems is critical to investigation and incident response
- malicious actors may attempt to create, rename, delete files so being able to notice normal vs. abnormal file location and disk usage is critical
- In environments like servers and remote shells CLI is fastest inspection method
